{
  "texts": [
    "This stage may begin 20 years before symptoms appear.",
    "An earlier AD experience study found significantly stronger connections between early linguistic skills and AD later in life (Bhandare et al., 2016).",
    "Stage two is modest cognitive impairment.",
    "Memory loss or other mental disability in those who can do most of their daily chores alone is called MCI (Sarraf et al., 2016).",
    "The patient's family and close friends may detect cognitive ability issues at this time, but they don't influence their everyday lives (Dubois et al., 2009)."
  ]
}